# Claude Context - Style Converter Project

> **READ THIS FILE FIRST** - Essential context for working on this project

## Project Summary

**Style-Converter** is a Kotlin/JVM CLI tool that converts JSON-based CSS-like style definitions into platform-specific UI code (Android Jetpack Compose and iOS SwiftUI).

**Current Status**: ✅ Parsing complete, 🎉 **NEW: Advanced Compose generator with ContentScope support integrated!**

## Key Architecture Points

### Pipeline Flow
```
JSON Input
  ↓
JsonInputParser (extract component data)
  ↓
PropertyValidator (validate CSS property names)
  ↓
ShorthandExpander (expand 62 shorthands → longhands)
  ↓
PropertyParser (parse to IRProperty instances from irmodels/)
SelectorParser (parse to IRSelector instances)
MediaQueryParser (parse to IRMedia instances)
  ↓
ComponentBuilder (assemble IRComponent from irmodels/)
  ↓
DocumentBuilder (assemble IRDocument from irmodels/)
  ↓
IR Model (IRDocument with 510 longhand properties)
  ↓
PropertyAnalyzer (detect wrapper needs: flex, position, scroll, SVG, etc.)
  ↓
ComponentStructureBuilder (build wrapper hierarchy + ContentScope)
  ↓
CodeGenerator (generate final Kotlin/Swift code)
  ↓
Platform Code (Compose/SwiftUI)
```

### Technology Stack
- **Language**: Kotlin 2.1.0
- **Runtime**: Java 21+
- **Build**: Gradle 8.14
- **JSON**: kotlinx.serialization-json 1.6.3
- **CLI**: `./gradlew run --args="convert --from css --to compose,swiftui -i <input> -o <outDir>"`

### NEW IR Model Structure (irmodels/ folder) - **510 LONGHAND PROPERTIES IMPLEMENTED**

**🎉 COMPREHENSIVE**: 510 longhand property files created representing 94.5% CSS coverage!

**IMPORTANT: Shorthands vs Longhands**
- ✅ **IR Model contains ONLY longhands** - Shorthand properties (margin, padding, border, flex, etc.) are NOT in the IR
- ✅ **Shorthands expanded during parsing** - ShorthandRegistry expands 50+ shorthands into longhands before IR creation
- ✅ **Example**: `margin: 10px 20px` → `margin-top: 10px`, `margin-right: 20px`, `margin-bottom: 10px`, `margin-left: 20px`
- ✅ **62 shorthands supported**: margin, padding, border*, flex, grid*, animation, transition, background, overflow, inset*, scroll-*, place-*, column-rule, list-style, mask*, and many logical properties

**Architecture Constraints:**
- ✅ **Pure data representation** - NO conversion logic in IR classes
- ✅ **ONE longhand property per file** - Each longhand CSS property gets its own dedicated file
  - Example: `FontSizeProperty.kt` handles ONLY `font-size`
  - Example: `ColorProperty.kt` handles ONLY `color`
  - Example: `PaddingTopProperty.kt` handles ONLY `padding-top` (NOT padding shorthand)
- ✅ **Maximum 100 lines per file** - Forces modular, maintainable code
- ✅ **Precise type constraints** - Use enums/sealed interfaces for exact valid values
  - Example: `text-align` accepts ONLY: start, end, left, right, center, justify, match-parent
  - Example: `font-weight` accepts ONLY: 100-900 (numeric) or normal/bold/lighter/bolder
- ✅ **Organized by category** - Grouped in folders (typography, color, spacing, etc.)
- ✅ **Fully serializable** - All types annotated with `@Serializable`

**Base Types (`irmodels/base/`):**
- `IRProperty` - Simple interface with only `propertyName` field
- `IRLength` - Value + unit enum (PX, DP, EM, REM, PERCENT, VW, VH, PT, CM, MM, IN, EX, CH, FR)
- `IRColor` - Sealed interface: Hex | RGB | HSL | Named | CurrentColor | Transparent
- `IRKeyword`, `IRUrl`, `IRPercentage`, `IRNumber`, `IRAngle`, `IRTime`

